/* Name : Ali Mohammad Jobaer
Student ID : 103835483 */
import React from 'react';
import { Container, Typography, Box, Paper, Divider } from '@mui/material';
import { BarChart, Bar, XAxis, YAxis, Tooltip, CartesianGrid } from 'recharts';

const Reports =() => {
  
  const data = [
      { name: 'Reentrancy Attacks', vulnerabilities: 3 },
      { name: 'Arithmetic Over/Underflows', vulnerabilities: 2 },
      { name: 'Gas Limitations', vulnerabilities: 1 }
  ];

  return (
      <Container maxWidth="lg">
          <Box marginTop={3} marginBottom={3}>
              <Typography variant="h4">Generated Report</Typography>
          </Box>
          {/* 
             Report Overview Section
             Displays general information about the audit. 
          */}
          <Paper elevation={3} sx={{ padding: '2rem', backgroundColor: '#984447' }}>
              <Typography variant="h5" gutterBottom>
                  Report Overview
              </Typography>
              <Typography variant="body1">Contract Name/ID: SampleContract123</Typography>
              <Typography variant="body1">Date of Audit: 12th August 2023</Typography>
          </Paper>

          {/* Vulnerabilities Section
             List of vulnerabilities categorized by their types. */}
          

          <Paper elevation={3} sx={{ padding: '2rem', marginTop: '2rem', backgroundColor: '#122C34' }}>
              <Typography variant="h5" gutterBottom>
                  Vulnerabilities
              </Typography>
              <Divider sx={{ margin: '1rem 0' }} />
              <Typography variant="h6">Category: Reentrancy Attacks</Typography>
              <Typography variant="body1">Vulnerability 1: The contract fails to use the checks-effects-interactions pattern, making it susceptible to reentrancy attacks.</Typography>
              <Typography variant="body1">Vulnerability 2: External function call made after changing the contract's state.</Typography>

              <Typography variant="h6" sx={{marginTop: '1rem'}}>Category: Arithmetic Over/Underflows</Typography>
              <Typography variant="body1">Vulnerability 1: Lack of 'SafeMath' library usage for uint operations.</Typography>
              <Typography variant="body1">Vulnerability 2: Potential underflow detected in a subtraction operation.</Typography>
          </Paper>

          {/* Vulnerabilities Bar Chart Section
             Visual representation of vulnerabilities by category. */}

          <Paper elevation={3} sx={{ padding: '2rem', marginTop: '2rem', backgroundColor: '#89BD9E' }}>
              <Typography variant="h5" gutterBottom>
                  Vulnerabilities by Category
              </Typography>

              <BarChart width={600} height={300} data={data}>
                  <CartesianGrid strokeDasharray="3 3" />
                  <XAxis dataKey="name" />
                  <YAxis />
                  <Tooltip />
                  <Bar dataKey="vulnerabilities" fill="#8884d8" />
              </BarChart>
          </Paper>

          {/* Suggestions Section
             Recommended fixes or improvements for identified vulnerabilities. */}

          <Paper elevation={3} sx={{ padding: '2rem', marginTop: '2rem', backgroundColor: '#9C914F' }}>
              <Typography variant="h5" gutterBottom>
                  Suggestions
              </Typography>
              <Divider sx={{ margin: '1rem 0' }} />
              <Typography variant="h6">Category: Reentrancy Attacks</Typography>
              <Typography variant="body1">Suggestion for Vulnerability 1: Implement checks-effects-interactions pattern and ensure external calls are the last thing done in the function.</Typography>
              <Typography variant="body1">Suggestion for Vulnerability 2: Refactor the logic to ensure state-changing operations occur after any external function calls.</Typography>

              <Typography variant="h6" sx={{marginTop: '1rem'}}>Category: Arithmetic Over/Underflows</Typography>
              <Typography variant="body1">Suggestion for Vulnerability 1: Integrate 'SafeMath' library for arithmetic operations to prevent overflows and underflows.</Typography>
              <Typography variant="body1">Suggestion for Vulnerability 2: Utilize appropriate checks or leverage 'SafeMath' to prevent potential underflows.</Typography>
          </Paper>
      </Container>
  );
}
export default Reports;
